Global 4,4'-Oxydiphthalic Anhydride (ODPA) Market Insights
4,4'-Oxydiphthalic Anhydride (ODPA) Market size was valued at USD 0.12 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 0.22 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

4,4'-Oxydiphthalic Anhydride (ODPA) Market Overview
The global 4,4'-Oxydiphthalic Anhydride (ODPA) market was valued at USD 1,294.8 million in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 2,255.3 million by 2032, growing at a CAGR of 6.36% from 2024 to 2032. This growth is driven by the increasing demand for high-performance polymers across various industries, including aerospace, automotive, and electronics. ODPA serves as a crucial monomer in the production of polyimides, which are essential for manufacturing lightweight, high-strength materials. The market's expansion is also influenced by technological advancements and the rising emphasis on sustainable production methods.

